cs.NI, cs.NE, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses TCP extensions and alternative transport protocols for high-speed networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.NE (Network and Communications) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of transport protocols in networks, which is a key aspect of network and communications research.
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, security is an important aspect of transport protocols and may be discussed in the context of TCP extensions and alternative protocols.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper may touch upon distributed computing and parallel processing in the context of improving transport protocol performance.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may discuss information theory concepts such as channel capacity and throughput in the context of evaluating transport protocol performance.
